<title>JAPAN: Mitsui Trust problem loans (Banking account).</title>
<headline>Mitsui Trust problem loans (Banking account).</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1996-11-25</dateline>
<text>
<p>Mitsui Trust &amp; Banking Co Ltd has disclosed its restructured loans (in billions of yen unless specified):</p>
<p>					end-Sep 96     end-Mar 96</p>
<p>  Restructured loans	     77.8	    328.3</p>
<p>  Bad loans			 142.2	     43.4</p>
<p>  Non-performing loans	  658.5	    621.9</p>
<p>  Total problem loans	   878.5	    993.6</p>
<p>Restructured loans are those on which interest rates have been cut to help corporate restructuring. Bad loans are to bankrupt firms and non-performing are those with interest payments in arrears by six months or more.</p>
</text>
